Unit</title><illustration reuse="all"><graphic file="..\..\Graphics\CGM\053J-732-005.cgm" cropped="1" float="0" height="5.70in" impsize="9.00in 5.70in"></graphic><title id="ID20065181313355627">VHF Radio Unit Replacement</title></illustration><safety reuse="all"><hazard level="notification" symbol="note"><hazard-desc>When performing maintenance, finding access doors unlocked
on normally-secured lockers or cabinets must be reported to supervision.</hazard-desc></hazard></safety><step><para reuse="all">Unlock and open Cab Car locker LC access
door using NJ Transit coach key.</para></step><safety reuse="all"><hazard level="warning" symbol="electrical"><hazard-desc>Cables connected to locker equipment can cause electrical
shock. Exercise care whenever accessing any of the electrical lockers.
Failure to do so may result in injury or death.</hazard-desc></hazard></safety><safety reuse="all"><hazard level="warning" symbol="electrical"><hazard-desc>The following steps are performed while some locker
equipment may be powered. Exercise care whenever near powered equipment.
Failure to do so may result in injury or death.</hazard-desc></hazard></safety><step><para reuse="all">Disconnect cable plug <verbatim>RADP1051</verbatim> (<ref-container><label>7</label><graphic-ref ref-id="CBBEFAIB" callout="7"></graphic-ref></ref-container>)
from unit VHF-type connector. </para></step><step><para reuse="all">Disconnect antenna cable plug <verbatim>RADP</verbatim> (<ref-container><label>8</label><graphic-ref ref-id="CBBEFAIB" callout="8"></graphic-ref></ref-container>)
from unit circular connector. </para></step></activity><activity><title id="ID20065181313357127">Remove Radio Assembly
From Mounting Base</title><step><para reuse="all">On each of left side and right side of
unit, loosen wing nut (<ref-container><label>10</label><graphic-ref ref-id="CBBEFAIB" callout="10"></graphic-ref></ref-container>)
and back out cylindrical holder (<ref-container><label>11</label><graphic-ref ref-id="CBBEFAIB" callout="11"></graphic-ref></ref-container>)
until clearing finger (<ref-container><label>12</label><graphic-ref ref-id="CBBEFAIB" callout="12"></graphic-ref></ref-container>).</para></step><step><para reuse="all">Remove radio unit (<ref-container><label>1</label><graphic-ref ref-id="CBBEFAIB" callout="1"></graphic-ref></ref-container>)
with adapter plate (<ref-container><label>9</label><graphic-ref ref-id="CBBEFAIB" callout="9"></graphic-ref></ref-container>)
as single assembly, as follows:</para><step><para reuse="all">Grab radio unit handle.</para></step><step><para reuse="all">Lift front of assembly at slight angle
to free interlocked retaining lips located at rear edge of adapter plate (<ref-container><label>9</label><graphic-ref ref-id="CBBEFAIB" callout="9"></graphic-ref></ref-container>)
and mounting base (<ref-container><label>6</label><graphic-ref ref-id="CBBEFAIB" callout="6"></graphic-ref></ref-container>). </para></step><step><para reuse="all">Pull radio unit with adapter plate (<ref-container><label>9</label><graphic-ref ref-id="CBBEFAIB" callout="9"></graphic-ref></ref-container>) and remove
from mounting base (<ref-container><label>6</label><graphic-ref ref-id="CBBEFAIB" callout="6"></graphic-ref></ref-container>). </para></step></step></activity><activity><title id="ID200651813133511427">Install Radio Assembly
On Mounting Base</title><step><para reuse="all">Position radio unit (<ref-container><label>1</label><graphic-ref ref-id="CBBEFAIB" callout="1"></graphic-ref></ref-container>)
with assembled adapter plate (<ref-container><label>9</label><graphic-ref ref-id="CBBEFAIB" callout="9"></graphic-ref></ref-container>)
on top of mounting base (<ref-container><label>6</label><graphic-ref ref-id="CBBEFAIB" callout="6"></graphic-ref></ref-container>). </para></step><step><para reuse="all">Grabbing radio unit handle, lift front
of assembly at slight angle.</para></step><step><para reuse="all">Push radio unit (rearwards until retaining
lips located at rear edge of both adapter plate (<ref-container><label>9</label><graphic-ref ref-id="CBBEFAIB" callout="9"></graphic-ref></ref-container>)
and mounting base (<ref-container><label>6</label><graphic-ref ref-id="CBBEFAIB" callout="6"></graphic-ref></ref-container>), make
contact and engage. Adjust lifting angle until retaining lips interlock.</para></step><step><para reuse="all">Let weight of radio unit rest on mounting base (<ref-container><label>6</label><graphic-ref ref-id="CBBEFAIB" callout="6"></graphic-ref></ref-container>).
Ensure rear retaining lips are securely interlocked.</para></step><step><para reuse="all">On each of left side and right side, engage
cylindrical holder (<ref-container><label>11</label><graphic-ref ref-id="CBBEFAIB" callout="11"></graphic-ref></ref-container>)
over retaining finger (<ref-container><label>12</label><graphic-ref ref-id="CBBEFAIB" callout="12"></graphic-ref></ref-container>) and
secure in place with wing nut (<ref-container><label>10</label><graphic-ref ref-id="CBBEFAIB" callout="10"></graphic-ref></ref-container>). </para></step></activity><activity><title id="ID200651813133519527">Reconnect VHF Radio
Unit</title><step><para reuse="all">Connect cable plug <verbatim>RADP1051</verbatim> (<ref-container><label>7</label><graphic-ref ref-id="CBBEFAIB" callout="7"></graphic-ref></ref-container>)
to radio unit circular connector.</para></step><step><para reuse="all">Connect antenna cable plug <verbatim>RADP</verbatim> (<ref-container><label>8</label><graphic-ref ref-id="CBBEFAIB" callout="8"></graphic-ref></ref-container>)
to radio unit VHF-type connector. </para></step><step><para reuse="all">Close and lock locker LC access door using
NJ Transit coach key.</para></step><step><para reuse="all">Restore power to VHF radio unit, switch
circuit breaker <verbatim>RADIO CB2</verbatim> to ON.</para></step></activity><follow-on-tasks><para reuse="all">Verify Radio Operation. Refer to <task-ref-group><task-ref-number e-list-number="09 01 01" giid-maint-item-desc="Cab Communication Control Panel" user-defined-1="" user-defined-2="" user-defined-3="" maint-item-desc="Cab Communication Control Panel"><miid>BOM01312</miid><task-code>A</task-code></task-ref-number></task-ref-group>.</para></follow-on-tasks></task></ib>